      <section id="main_content" class="inner">
        <h3><a id="welcome" class="anchor" href="#welcome" aria-hidden="true"><span aria-hidden="true" class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Welcome to EpicMode</h3>
		<p>EpicMode is an open source project to design clothing from measurements to manufacturing using 3D tools.</p>

		<h3><a id="epicmode-consortium" class="anchor" href="#epicmode-consortium" aria-hidden="true"><span aria-hidden="true" class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>EpicMode Consortium</h3>
		<p>Companies, Universities, NGOs, and Individuals are joining hands to make this project available to everyone.</p>

		<h3><a id="irl-or-digital-you-decide" class="anchor" href="#irl-or-digital-you-decide" aria-hidden="true"><span aria-hidden="true" class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>IRL or digital, you decide</h3>
		<p>Use EpicMode to create clothing IRL for yourself or others. Or use EpicMode to create clothing for your 3D characters. Dress yourself and your character in the same design!</p>

		<h3><a id="authors-and-contributors" class="anchor" href="#authors-and-contributors" aria-hidden="true"><span aria-hidden="true" class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Authors and Contributors</h3>
		<p>Want to be a contributor? Send email to <a href="mailto:love@epicmode.co">love@epicmode.co</a></br>
		Want to join the consortium? Send email to <a href="mailto:superlove@epicmode.co">superlove@epicmode.co</a></p>
